<h1>3 User Management Module</h1>
<p>This module allows a system administrator to manage (to enter or update) the user information.</p>

<div id="3.1">
<p>System administrators can register new users for the radiology information system.</p>
<p>Clicking the "<b>+User Account</b>" hyperlink will directe system administrators to the New User Register page.</p>

<p>You need to provide the following information:</p>

<ul>
	<li>User Name</li>
	<li>Password</li>
	<li>User Class*</li>
	<li>Choose Person**</li>
</ul>

<p>* &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="code">Choose one from "Administrator", "Doctor", "Radiologist" and "Patient"</span>.</br>

** <span class="code">Choose a Person from the database. See <a href="3.3_register_person.html">3.3 Register New Person</a> and <a href="3.4_update_person.html">3.4 Update Personal Information</a> for more information</span>.</p>

<p>Click the "<b>Add</b>" button to register. Click the "<b>cancel</b>" button to cancel the registration.</p>
</div>

<div id="3.2">
<h2>3.2 Run Tomcat</h2>
<ul>
	<li><p>Open a terminal, and run <span class="code">starttomcat</span></p></li>
</ul>
</div>

<div id="3.3">
<h2>3.3 Set up the initial database</h2>
<ul>
	<li><p>Start <span class="code">sqlplus</span> in a termial and login.</p></li>
	<li><p>Set up and populate the initial database using script files (e.g. <span class="code">setup.sql</span>) by running the following commands: </br>
		<span class="code">@setup.sql</span> </br>
</ul>
</div>

<div id="3.4">
<h2>3.4 Connect to Oracle DB</h2>
<ul>
	<li><p>You need to connect to Oracle DB at <span class="code">http://HostName:PORT/proj/Connector.html</span> where <span class="code">HostName</span> is the machine name of the server the system installed on and <span class="code">PORT</span> is the port number that tomcat is running on.</p></li>
	<li><p>Enter the <b>Oracle ID</b> and <b>Password</b>, and click "<b>CONNECT</b>" button</p></li>
</ul>
</div>

<div id="3.5">
<h2>3.5 Connect to Oracle DB</h2>
<ul>
	<li><p>You need to connect to Oracle DB at <span class="code">http://HostName:PORT/proj/Connector.html</span> where <span class="code">HostName</span> is the machine name of the server the system installed on and <span class="code">PORT</span> is the port number that tomcat is running on.</p></li>
	<li><p>Enter the <b>Oracle ID</b> and <b>Password</b>, and click "<b>CONNECT</b>" button</p></li>
</ul>
</div>

